our newest product on Nx Cloud: Tusky."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-center","children":[" ",["$","iframe",null,{"src":"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Xfvv09wSoM8?si=jnzyLHtdWBLwx_U0","title":"Tusky","width":"100%","allow":"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; fullscreen","loading":"lazy","className":"mb-1 rounded-lg shadow-lg"}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Tusky is an Artificial Intelligence for your codebase, and it will be available on Nx Cloud soon — starting in Spring of 2024."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"In the teaser video, you can see some ways Tusky will be integrated into Nx Cloud to provide explainations on failed tasks, or cache misses."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The more exciting features of Tusky though includes the ability to perfectly optimize the number of agents used per PR — even spinning up and tearing down agents mid-pipeline! This is a huge optimization for task distribution, and will help optimize both walltime of your CI, as well as compute costs!"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Tusky will also be able to provide organizational-level insights to your codebase, including automatically detecting development groups (like lines of business) inside your codebase based on commit history, and providing statistical insights on their commit patterns. We’re also excited about Tusky being able to make suggestions on things you can do to further optimize your codebase — like generating a PR to introduce ",["$","$La",null,{"prefetch":false,"href":"https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners","passHref":true,"replace":false,"scroll":true,"shallow":false,"children":"Codeowners","target":"_blank","rel":"noreferrer","className":"text-blue-600 transition-colors ease-out hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-sky-500 dark:hover:text-sky-400"}]," to the repo!"]}],["$","h2",null,{"id":"nx-release-is-stable","className":"group scroll-mt-20","children":["Nx Release Is Stable",["$","$La",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#nx-release-is-stable","children":["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","strokeWidth":1.5,"stroke":"currentColor","aria-hidden":"true","data-slot":"icon","aria-labelledby":"$undefined","className":"mb-1 ml-2 inline h-5 w-5 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100","children":[null,["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","d":"M13.19 8.688a4.5 4.5 0 0 1 1.242 7.244l-4.5 4.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-6.364-6.364l1.757-1.757m13.35-.622 1.757-1.757a4.5 4.5 0 0 0-6.364-6.364l-4.5 4.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 0 1.242 7.244"}]]}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Versioning and publishing packages is always a bit tricky. Mix in the added complexity of having multiple packages — sometimes with different versioning or publishing strategies — inside the same codebase, and things can get weird quick!"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["For a long time, Nx has been purposefully versioning and publishing agnostic, but given our time spent as ",["$","$La",null,{"prefetch":false,"href":"https://blog.nrwl.io/lerna-is-dead-long-live-lerna-61259f97dbd9","passHref":true,"replace":false,"scroll":true,"shallow":false,"children":"stewards of Lerna","target":"_blank","rel":"noreferrer","className":"text-blue-600 transition-colors ease-out hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-sky-500 dark:hover:text-sky-400"}]," (the OG Javascript monorepo tool), we’ve been able to take alot of that experience and finally feel confident creating our own versioning and publishing implementation."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Therefore, we’ve been working on a new command to the Nx CLI: ",["$","$La",null,{"prefetch":false,"href":"/recipes/nx-release/get-started-with-nx-release#get-started-with-nx-release","passHref":true,"replace":false,"scroll":true,"shallow":false,"children":"nx release","target":"$undefined","rel":"$undefined","className":"text-blue-600 transition-colors ease-out hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-sky-500 dark:hover:text-sky-400"}],". We launched this on Friday of our Launch Nx week!"]}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Juri goes into ",["$","$La",null,{"prefetch":false,"href":"/blog/versioning-and-releasing-packages-in-a-monorepo","passHref":true,"replace":false,"scroll":true,"shallow":false,"children":"full details in this blog post","target":"$undefined","rel":"$undefined","className":"text-blue-600 transition-colors ease-out hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-sky-500 dark:hover:text-sky-400"}],", and James Henry — our Director of Engineering and the primary engineer responsible for both maintaining Lerna and creating Nx Release — expands further in his conference talk:"]}],["$","h3",null,{"id":"conference-talk-releasing-nx-release","className":"group scroll-mt-20","children":["Conference Talk: Releasing Nx Release",["$","$La",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#conference-talk-releasing-nx-release","children":["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","fill":"none","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","strokeWidth":1.5,"stroke":"currentColor","aria-hidden":"true","data-slot":"icon","aria-labelledby":"$undefined","className":"mb-1 ml-2 inline h-5 w-5 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100","children":[null,["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","d":"M13.19 8.688a4.5 4.5 0 0 1 1.242 7.244l-4.5 4.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-6.364-6.364l1.757-1.757m13.35-.622 1.757-1.757a4.5 4.5 0 0 0-6.364-6.364l-4.5 4.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 0 1.242 7.244"}]]}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Speaker:"}]," ",["$","$La",null,{"prefetch":false,"href":"https://twitter.com/MrJamesHenry","passHref":true,"replace":false,"scroll":true,"shallow":false,"children":"James Henry","target":"_blank","rel":"noreferrer","className":"text-blue-600 transition-colors ease-out hover:text-blue-700 dark:text-sky-500 dark:hover:text-sky-400"}]," | ",["$","$La",null,{"prefetch":false,"href":"https://github.com/JamesHenry/nx-release-cmd","passHr